snippet.textDisplay:
It is true that people who are healthy do not need masks, but sadly not everyone thinks like this.
People often self-diagnose and refuse to admit having symptoms of the virus, and when these said people DO NOT wear a mask when they're in the public, and actually healthy people are not wearing masks either, there is a risk of healthy people contracting the virus spread by those who think they are fine but are not.
I'm from Hong Kong, so trust me when I say a lot of people in Hong Kong who are sick do not think they are sick.

I do agree however that people should not panic and go stockpiling masks, they should only keep a necessary amount of masks in their home, and let people who really need masks be able to buy masks with a reasonable price.
